<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="66" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1281,2034]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1281,1306]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[351,409,1281,1305]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[423,486,1281,1306]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Head</emphasis>
. Brown; eye bridge 
<number box="[716,730,1281,1305]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="4.0">4</number>
facets wide. Antenna unicolourous brown except yellow scape and pedicel; basal part of 
<number box="[451,465,1320,1344]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="4.0">4</number>
th flagellomere 
<number box="[637,721,1319,1344]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="2.95" valueMax="3.3" valueMin="2.6">2.6–3.3</number>
times as long as wide, total length of 
<number box="[1166,1180,1320,1344]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="4.0">4</number>
th flagellomere 
<number box="[1352,1435,1320,1344]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="3.5" valueMax="3.9" valueMin="3.1">3.1–3.9</number>
times as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[408,477,1355,1380]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1982,2005]" captionTargetBox="[214,1380,216,1951]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[193,1394,193,1969]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 7. Bradysia similigibbosa, holotype, male. 3. 4 th flagellomere, lateral. 4. Tibial organ on inner-side of foretibia. 5. Wing. 6. Gonostylus, ventral. 7. Hypopygium, ventral. Scale bars: Figs 3, 4, 6, 7 = 0.1 mm; Fig. 5 = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285014/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[461,477,1356,1380]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
); necks of flagellomeres bicoloured, edges contrasting brown to pale base; basal part of flagellomeres without sensilla. Maxillary palpus yellow slightly darker than scape and pedicel; segment 
<number box="[1422,1436,1392,1416]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
usually longer than segment 
<number box="[478,492,1428,1452]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
with 
<number box="[558,601,1428,1452]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
bristles and a dorsal flat patch of sensilla, segment 
<number box="[1191,1205,1428,1452]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
with one long outer bristle, segment 
<number box="[337,351,1464,1488]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="3.0">3</number>
longest, 
<number box="[455,490,1463,1488]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times longer than segment 
<number box="[804,819,1464,1488]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[833,922,1463,1488]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[938,1005,1463,1488]" captionStart="FIGURES 1, 2" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1188,1211]" captionTargetBox="[262,1326,534,1168]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[246,1341,515,1178]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1, 2. Habitus of males, genitalia removed, lateral. 1. Bradysia similigibbosa, holotype. 2. Bradysia irwini, holotype. Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285013/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[992,1005,1464,1488]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pale brown in contrast to the brown head. Posterior pronotum bare. Anterior pronotum with 
<number box="[782,825,1499,1524]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3–6</number>
bristles. Episternum 
<number box="[1064,1078,1500,1524]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
with 
<number box="[1143,1199,1499,1524]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="10.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="6.0">6–14</number>
bristles. Mesonotum with some stronger dorsocentrals and with 
<number box="[640,681,1535,1560]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
long and some weaker laterals. Scutellum with 
<number box="[1228,1242,1536,1560]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="4.0">4</number>
strong and some minor bristles. Katepisternum slightly longer than high. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[776,841,1571,1596]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[855,923,1571,1596]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1982,2005]" captionTargetBox="[214,1380,216,1951]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[193,1394,193,1969]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 7. Bradysia similigibbosa, holotype, male. 3. 4 th flagellomere, lateral. 4. Tibial organ on inner-side of foretibia. 5. Wing. 6. Gonostylus, ventral. 7. Hypopygium, ventral. Scale bars: Figs 3, 4, 6, 7 = 0.1 mm; Fig. 5 = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285014/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[907,923,1571,1596]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). Length = 
<quantity box="[1053,1191,1571,1596]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.45" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="2.45" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="2.3">2.3–2.6 mm</quantity>
; width/length = 
<number pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="0.375" valueMax="0.39" valueMin="0.36">0.36– 0.39</number>
. Wing membrane transparent, without macrotrichia; anal area well developed; veins distinct except weak mstem; all posterior veins without macrotrichia; R and R 
<number box="[800,808,1658,1672]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
with dorsal macrotrichia only; apical part of R 
<number box="[1367,1375,1658,1672]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="5.0">5</number>
with ventral and dorsal macrotrichia; R 
<number box="[546,554,1697,1711]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
/R = 
<number box="[610,725,1682,1707]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="0.78" valueMax="0.86" valueMin="0.7">0.70–0.86</number>
; c/w = 
<number box="[810,925,1682,1707]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="0.625" valueMax="0.67" valueMin="0.58">0.58–0.67</number>
; r-m/bM = 
<number box="[1056,1172,1682,1707]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="0.77" valueMax="0.9" valueMin="0.64">0.64–0.90</number>
. Halteres yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1380,1436,1682,1707]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Legs</emphasis>
yellow; coxal bristles pale. Foretibia with some longer bristles within vestiture; tibial organ on foretibia (
<figureCitation box="[1358,1428,1721,1746]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1982,2005]" captionTargetBox="[214,1380,216,1951]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[193,1394,193,1969]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 7. Bradysia similigibbosa, holotype, male. 3. 4 th flagellomere, lateral. 4. Tibial organ on inner-side of foretibia. 5. Wing. 6. Gonostylus, ventral. 7. Hypopygium, ventral. Scale bars: Figs 3, 4, 6, 7 = 0.1 mm; Fig. 5 = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285014/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[1413,1428,1722,1746]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
) with a comb-like row of bristles wider than half of tibial apex width. All tibial spurs long; spurs of midtibia and hind tibia equal. Claws with fine teeth. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[596,713,1793,1818]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[729,795,1793,1818]" captionStart="FIGURES 1, 2" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1188,1211]" captionTargetBox="[262,1326,534,1168]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[246,1341,515,1178]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1, 2. Habitus of males, genitalia removed, lateral. 1. Bradysia similigibbosa, holotype. 2. Bradysia irwini, holotype. Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285013/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[782,795,1794,1818]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pale brown, same colour as thorax, sometimes slightly darker. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[236,391,1829,1854]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Hypopygium</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[407,476,1829,1854]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1982,2005]" captionTargetBox="[214,1380,216,1951]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[193,1394,193,1969]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 7. Bradysia similigibbosa, holotype, male. 3. 4 th flagellomere, lateral. 4. Tibial organ on inner-side of foretibia. 5. Wing. 6. Gonostylus, ventral. 7. Hypopygium, ventral. Scale bars: Figs 3, 4, 6, 7 = 0.1 mm; Fig. 5 = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285014/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[460,476,1830,1854]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). As brown as abdomen. Gonocoxites wider than long, with normal setosity; ventral, inner-side of gonocoxites u-shaped and lighter, without basal lobe of bristles. Gonostylus (
<figureCitation box="[1175,1243,1865,1890]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1982,2005]" captionTargetBox="[214,1380,216,1951]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[193,1394,193,1969]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 7. Bradysia similigibbosa, holotype, male. 3. 4 th flagellomere, lateral. 4. Tibial organ on inner-side of foretibia. 5. Wing. 6. Gonostylus, ventral. 7. Hypopygium, ventral. Scale bars: Figs 3, 4, 6, 7 = 0.1 mm; Fig. 5 = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285014/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[1229,1243,1865,1890]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
) 
<number box="[1260,1295,1865,1890]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="2.5">2.5</number>
to 3.0 times as long as wide, basal and apical inner-side of gonostylus impressed, widest at middle; apex of gonostylus distinctly tapered and with a subapical group of 
<number box="[714,728,1938,1962]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="4.0">4</number>
long spines, and one apical spine on the adjacent outer side. Tegmen trapezoidal, with long and strongly sclerotized basal apodemes; area of teeth large, with numerous strong, triangular teeth. Ejaculatory apodeme short and strong.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285014/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" targetBox="[214,1380,216,1951]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1982,2035]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,315,1982,2005]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">FIGURES 3–7.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[322,557,1983,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similigibbosa">
<emphasis box="[322,557,1983,2005]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Bradysia similigibbosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, holotype, male. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[735,754,1983,2004]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">3.</emphasis>
4th flagellomere, lateral. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1018,1037,1983,2004]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">4.</emphasis>
Tibial organ on inner-side of foretibia. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,170,2014,2035]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">5.</emphasis>
Wing. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[244,263,2014,2035]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">6.</emphasis>
Gonostylus, ventral. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[480,499,2014,2035]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">7.</emphasis>
Hypopygium, ventral. Scale bars: Figs 3, 4, 6, 7 = 0.1 mm; Fig. 5 = 1 mm.
</paragraph>
